Package app.Models

Class ClientConfig

java.lang.Object
app.Models.ClientConfig
public class ClientConfig extends Object
Represents the configuration settings for a client in a sensor network. This class encapsulates the configuration parameters required to setup and operate a client, including connections and operational parameters.

      public ClientConfig(String inboundPortRegister, String uriClock, int name, List<fr.sorbonne_u.cps.sensor_network.interfaces.RequestI> requests, String requestNodeName)
      Constructs a new ClientConfig with specified parameters.
      Parameters:
      inboundPortRegister - The inbound port on the registry for this client.
      uriClock - The URI of the clock server to synchronize time-sensitive operations.
      name - A numeric identifier for the client, used in logging and management.
      requests - A list of RequestI objects representing the requests the client will perform.
      requestNodeName - The default node from which the client will request data.
